    Runs the model fitting (fit) on data multiple times and returns the paramaters with the highest loglikelihood

    fit_mutliple.Rd

    Run the model on data multiple times (n) and returns the model with the largest likelihood. This allows for a more comprehensive search of the model sample space.

    fit_mutliple(
  distance,
  model = "collective",
  n = 5,
  upper = 5,
  bounds = NULL,
  verbose_r = FALSE,
  verbose_cpp = FALSE,
  xtol = 0
)

    Arguments

    distance

    doubleArray The distance decoded from the waggle dance.

    model

    characterArray The model to run (collective or individual). Defaults to collective.

    n

    integer The number of models to run

    upper

    double The upper parameter bound. Defaults to 5.

    bounds

    named list user supplied bounds. Defaults to NULL. If null the bounds are automatically generated.

    verbose_r

    Bool, to display R function evaluations, defaults to FALSE

    verbose_cpp

    Bool, to display C function evaluations, defaults to FALSE

    xtol

    double, The absolute tolerance on function value. If 0 (default) then default to nlopt default value.
